So I was gonna do it for 7 days but I ended a day early. I had minestrone soup this morning. But the krishna lunch killed me. It almost felt worse than the latter part of the cleanse. i won't bother with the details. Someone told me I lost weight. and it was confirmed today when my tight shorts fit and i didnt have to leave the top button undone. for anyone who is considering doin the cleanse. do not do it for weight loss...half of it is water weight. anyways i do feel like eating healthier, portioned meals. and im pumped for working out again. i have been missing that. For anyone who needs a guide for eating right and working out join the self challenge on www.self.com 

SO today is a pretty busy day but that's how i like it. 

8:30-12:35 class, krishna lunch, study
4 study for religions test
5:10- 6 internship meeting thing..doubt ill go 
work out
8 heal the world meeting at cse 220
study, shower, PROJECT RUNWAY WITH THE GIRLS (tony will be in jax, i hope he reads this)and maybe xs to begin my weekend!

In other good news, the ebay dispute i was having was resolved. I sold a pair of jeans that came out to $31 something and they guy said he didnt get them and he wanted his money back. i was stupid and shipped it without a tracking number. if it didnt get resolved by tomorrow he was gonna get his money automatically. but i just got a message from him saying he got the jeans. whew! im sellin 3 other things now. so hopefully  i'll have a few bucks in a week. 

Lotsa birthdays today...AYLIN! DANE! CAM! PURVI! i hope i didnt miss anyone. love to all

pretty uneventful lazy sunday. woke up pretty early again but not with as much energy as yesterday. i didnt feel bad either. i reread up on the master cleanse and am gonna go back to it in the strictest sense...cos we had cheated a lil by eating fruit and such. the reading made the whole thing more sense than ever. 

At night, eli, norma, winnie and i went to the atlantic for the photo exhibit which inspired me to get my pictures enlarged and printed on nice paper. we all decided we need to do art once a week at least for an hr b/c i was complaining about how there is so much i want to do but don't make time for. today was successful in that sense because emma came over and i used myriams sewing machine to make this big shirt fit me right. not quite a porject but took me a bit cos im not used to the sewing machine. anyways the shirt looks great. good weekend. did no hw. yay. gonna go get myself in bed now and read a lil.

Today was AWESOME. I woke up at 8 30 and was full of energy. I laid in bed and red the magazine that annie gave me for valentines day. when i got up I realized how much energy I had. I cleaned my desk thorougly. like a mad woman infact. then i washed a sink load of dishes and wiped the kitchen down. i dumped out my back pack to clean that out but never really got to it. ohh yea i made alot of lists. i was going CRAZY. cos it was SUCH a beautiful day i had all the windows and doors open, as did my neighbors. i heard them downstairs so i went to see what was up. we all decided to spread blankets in the grass and read. I tried to teach myself spanish. Chris' family was in town so the boa constricter was out slithering around and his lil bro was running around. it was cute and fun. after i got to hot i lounged around the apt in my striped bathing suit and blue shorts that i love. of course i wasted a good amount of  time online. but earlier i got this crazy idea to paint my room. so yea. that happened. just one wall though. Danny helped me paint and he came up with the idea to paint random square on it. i must say it looks quite good.
Master cleanse sucked today. It was so hard. I am obsessed with food. can't wait till it gets better.

Last night I had the tea and this morning I did the saline wash. I messed up on the lemonade so it tastes awful but I can't waste it cos the maple syrup is pricey. Anyone who says they have more energy right away is just imagining it. good for them though. i feel the same just hungry. I am obsessed with the thought of food. I would say today is about self control. Nothing has really happened inside. or at least i cant tell yet

Overall things are going well. I mean of course there's always some bad things. but who wants to dwell on that? not me and not now. I actually had a valentine this year. It's been a long time since that has happened. I'm pretty happy. He's good to me. We went farahs for dinner and hookah then hung out with some friends. Last week I had 2 tests and a paper so I was really stressed but I did alright. A 80 % on the comp. politics test and 88% on my public relations test. not great but it's ok. I will be better about the next tests and i'll be fine.

I have a test and a paper due friday but I am already workin' on the reading instead of doing that night before thing like last week. The paper shouldn't be too bad.

Tomorrow I will begin a 10 day master cleanse which will clear out my toxins. kinda nervous, kinda excited. After that I want to make sure I eat really healthy and stay away from habits that are bad for my body. I have already been working out alot so i'm feeling good in that sense.

i love and hate when a song reminds me of someone. 

What song reminds you of someone? It could be a could be a good or bad reminder. You dont have to mention who it is. i think it'd be cool to see what the responses are.

2. Open the book to page 123.
3. Find the fifth sentence.
4. Post the text of the sentence in your journal along with these instructions.
5. Don't search around and look for the coolest book you can find. Do what's actually next to you.

i love ruby tuesdays, chad, erin, kimron (?), 1 1/2 hr breaks, overnighters, inventory, the mighty ducks (buncha quacks), lagoons...what else? ohh yea the ppl i work with

i am in need of a change. a huge momentous change.

i think the emotional state has begun. because as soon as she left i was really sad. i feel so selfish. and now im gonna either try to keep myself occupied till he gets back from work by reading bio or something. or just go to sleep. i really hope he isnt going out tonight. im being selfish again. i dont care.

so new school year so much to say about that. so much to say about the last few days. they havent really been the best. but thats not what im hear to talk about. all this lead me to these thoughts

i have an amazing best friend. and whether she likes it or not shes gets so hear just about every damn thing going on. but in a summarized version because she doesnt live in the same city. but not being in the same city prevents somethings. you just have to be there for some of it. i wish she was. im glad b is around. he gets to be there for everything and she get to hear it. :D <3

side note: i got the gorillaz song from marc, i dont know if this was a good request for me to make, cos it could torture me.

sometimes i think we just deal with the mirage because it feels better. not that the actuality would be a bad thing either, maybe just a void of all these awesome feelings. it is so easy to get it all confused though. this time i know the distinction. but will i always?  how many times am i going to do this to myself?

i think i would feel better if there were reciprication. but ive seen the old way and thats not what ive got. stupid little things are annoying  me. but these stupid little things shouldnt even happen.

im mad at myself for even writing this much about this. i know what it is and i should just continue being easy going about it. just lax

p.s. i dyed my some of my hair pink

it has been forever and a year since i have really posted. i mean REAL stuff going on. so i guess this is the best way to get back into the swing of lj, no point in catching up with the past month (??). sigh i dont even know how long its been. here it goes

WED- pleasantly surprised by marc being in town. the whole night was weird though. house. limo. club. empty. shamrocks. car? stadium. cops! it was soooo late by the time i got to bed, but somehow i made it up to study chem in the AM and go to work. 

THUR- rough. i was so beat tired. after classes i went to the mall with annie and some people to check my work schedule at A&F and they had def switched out the huge posters of the models. so i snagged one and hid it in the shady mafia guy's carpet store. why does everything feel like a blur now? it was only a few days ago. but just lotsa chilling. april fools joke that didnt go as planned. but then more chillin at the apt. 

SAT- the plan was marc, billy, briton, and i were gonna meet up at jason's place around 7ish. that def didnt happen. esp the marc meeting up at jasons. i couldnt get a ride to jasons but then whoa who calls---JULIE! she and i went down to 5 pts and go to car.connection while waiting for the peeps. and i got the enon cd 75% off. freakin awesome. go track 5. so everyone gets there and we go to fuel for the evergreen terrace show. it was crazy but so much fun. i def crowd surfed for the first time---woooooot. so did j tuck. yay. 

not a great entry but it had to be done. 

p.s. miami (south beach bhangra) was awesome. so i have awesome pics from then and wed/thu

as sick as it sounds im almost jealous of her. i mean i feel bad and everything. it shouldnt have happened. but oh how id love to care about someONE so much that i say those things she said. i care about my friends and my family, alot actually. i always want to be there for them. if i ever knew that i was a let down as a friend id prolly hate myself for it.  

=====================================================

so the other day i got this idea about "things working out in the end". i have always been a strong believer in it but i couldnt account for everything before "the end". sometimes it feels like what's the point of the end being okay if everything on the way could suck. but its all persepective. being short term shafted is okay. NO QUOTE!!

every now and then you have to get yourself out of a rut. you cant wait for things to change. just change something small. like the type music youre listening to. stop waiting around for things. but be ready for when things happen. try not to be caught off guard.

last but not least...i know i complain alot. ALOT. a good indicator of how close of a friend you are is how much i complain to you. usually i complain about little stupid things, stuff that gets resolved in a short time. the really big stuff i usually pent up. but i guess even those things have to come out sometime. and the lucky one was marco. i really appreciate you, alot.

"...but it's hard to stay mad when there's so much beauty in the world. Sometimes I feel like I'm seeing it all at once, and it's too much. My heart fills up like a balloon that's about to burst ... And then I remember ... to relax, and not try to hold on to it. And then it flows through me like rain. And I can't feel anything but gratitude for every single moment of my stupid little life. You have no idea what I'm talking about, I'm sure. Don't worry ... you will someday."

You Don't Have a Boyfriend Because You are Too Picky

You have no problem attracting guys - and even dating a little
It's just around second or third date time where you start to see faults
If a guy isn't near perfect, you're not into him.
It's good to have standards - but yours rule almost everyone out.

There are so many things from the past few days that i wanted to LJ about but it comes time to wrap things up for the year. 2004 was awesome for many reasons. it spans two great times---senior year and the start of college. i have loved many, missed many and met so many more. 

I hope everyone has a safe and happy holiday season and a smashin new years. i'll see some of you back home and the rest when i get back. 

love,

I wish I was a neutron bomb, for once I could go off 
I wish I was a sacrifice but somehow still lived on 
I wish I was a sentimental ornament you hung on 
The Christmas tree, I wish I was the star that went on top 
I wish I was the evidence, I wish I was the grounds 
For 50 million hands upraised and open toward the sky 

I wish I was a sailor with someone who waited for me 
I wish I was as fortunate, as fortunate as me 
I wish I was a messenger and all the news was good 
I wish I was the full moon shining off a Camaro's hood 

I wish I was an alien at home behind the sun 
I wish I was the souvenir you kept your house key on 
I wish I was the pedal brake that you depended on 
I wish I was the verb 'to trust' and never let you down 

I wish I was a radio song, the one that you turned up 
I wish, I wish, I wish, I wish 
I guess it never stops...

-pearl jam

i am insecure.
i am selfish.
i want to not care as much.
i'm settling for what ive got.
i am rude.
i complain alot.
im needy.
i feel sick.
i wish i was as witty as alice.

sometimes i look back and question if its all real. with some of them i feel the realness developing.
i go back to the gold because i know its real. there are no games to play. no frontin. 

ive told people, id rather be with a good friend (even if they are annoying me) than anywhere else in the world.
last night i was on the phone with someone i care about and miss alot. and that person didnt even know it but by the end of the convo i was tearing up. you did say the best thing tonight. i asked that you tell me to stop the way i was acting. 

i must be stubborn or something. this idea parallels me rather making a realization about a close friend then trying to meet random people.
 

on a side note i am obsessed with the garden state soundtrack.

when you feel like things suck, the good things seem so much better. 
it was nice to go over to shawn and davids with the girls. and i was surprised to see bernard and especially logan. she's always so cute. patrick called about my test. and later joe franco called to see how it went and to check up on me. it was a sweet pleasant surprise. he's a good guy. i feel like everytime things are kinda on the down all i have is my friends' love to keep me going.

i feel like i go through these emotional ups and downs. since my realization i was up and wasnt going anywhere soon. but nothing really happened since right after my realization--no on to blame.  i think im on my way down. this chem test was just a catalyst. there are plenty of other things that have culminated to a mass sadness. 

you and i, we cant even talk anymore, i mean we talk but its not a normal conversation. you probably wont read this and even if you did you would have no idea that its about you

and you i dont even know what to say. i read it and i didnt even know what to think. i honestly wouldnt care if it were anyone else. but ugh. pls. i care about you, dont be a hypocrite, at least not about that.

im not tired of the ppl care about. im tired of the stupid things they do. and im kinda tired of the fact that i care (about what they do).

side note...m.p., it was nice talkin at the r.u. today.

tonight i love faith, agatha, mel, annie, franco, patrick, mj, matt r. and nicole.

don't ever leave the one u love for the one u like, because the one u like will leave u for the one they love.

i talked to him and he told me his story. it was almost like a tease or a suggestion to me. but this seize the moment thing only works in retrospect.when youre in the moment there is too much other stuff going on, all the variables.

i made a toast tonight. i really wanted to do it at cafe carmon, with everyone but the table was too long and i didnt want to scream in such a nice setting. : ) so i did it for a smaller audience at teh casbah.it went something like:
"earlier at dinner this evening trevor picks up a piece of lemon, and says to me "watch this"
as he throws it at katie. then katie says "somethings just dont change". they dont, and i hope
the same for our friendships. i hope we develop these friendships for an immense amount
of time. (i remember saying immense cos after i said it was like what kinda word did i pick)
::people start raising glasses, general commontion:: also, ...im not done guys...we were
just talking and we think this should be a tradition done ever thanksgiving break...so heres
to friends getting together. cheers!"

SUN
today was blah. we meant to leave by 10 in the am but that didnt happen. eventually we got into this situation where my mom was like take the greyhound back. i was humored by the whole situation. not just the greyhound part. one sad note of the weekend. i did not get to see will, but hopefully he'll come to jax over winterbreak. i did get his dormline # from his dad so ill holla at him. ohhi just remembered another thing, i didnt see mehul...got lost in downtown for the bitch.   : D but id do it again.
i got back and no one was here. i chilled with emily and erin. i have the coolest RA ever.
